    <h1>Hash Functions</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Wikipedia &middot; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptographic_hash_function"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Cryptographic hash function</a> &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>cryptographic hash function</strong> maps arbitrary-length input to a fixed-length output. It must be one-way (hard to invert), collision-resistant (hard to find two inputs with the same hash), and avalanche-prone (a small input change flips about half the output bits).</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: input -> hash function -> fixed-length output -->
